definition: many/much/often/a lot of/numerous/more/in excess/how (to what extent)/multi-/Taiwan pr. [duo2] when it means "how"

sentences.english: Since founded more than 20 years ago, we put all our efforts on produce high quality multi-functional tools.
sentences.chinese: 本公司建厂二十多年来不断专注于开拓高质量的产品。

sentences.english: But that was over twenty years ago.
sentences.chinese: 但那是二十多年前的事情了。

sentences.english: Aside from my room, there are two dozens of rooms in this courtyard.
sentences.chinese: 除了我这房间，大院里还有二十多间房呢。

sentences.english: Indeed, over the past two decades, the family has dramatically reduced its stake.
sentences.chinese: 过去二十多年来，班氏家族一直在减持股份。

sentences.english: The life of Shubert has altogether created more than 20 piano sonatas.

sentences.english: China a spared more than two billion yuan for the fight against SARA.

sentences.chinese: 二十多年定居巴黎，戴海鹰是极认真的画家。

sentences.english: Twenty years has passed since Tangshan was hit by earthquake.
sentences.chinese: 唐山遭受地震以来二十多年已经过去了。

sentences.chinese: 这项法律被搁置了二十多年。

sentences.english: During his life, he saw the sale of more than twenty million of his ant colonies.
sentences.chinese: 在他的一生中，他看到了二十多万，他蚁群出售。
